Definition.WordDefinition:
Eventual \E*ven"tu*al\, a. [Cf. F. ['e]ventiel. See {Event}.] 1. Coming or happening as a consequence or result; consequential. --Burke. [1913 Webster]
2. Final; ultimate. ``Eventual success.'' --Cooper. [1913 Webster]
3. (Law) Dependent on events; contingent. --Marshall. [1913 Webster]

eventual adj : expected to follow in the indefinite future from causes already operating; "hope of eventual (or ultimate) rescue"; "if this trend continues it is not reasonable to expect the eventual collapse of the stock market" [syn: {eventual(a)}]
